  "prompt": "Does Quora censor questions?",
  "response": "Quora does have moderation policies in place that can lead to the removal or censorship of questions and answers. This is done to ensure that content adheres to community guidelines and standards regarding topics like hate speech, harassment, misinformation, and other violations. Users can report questions or answers they find inappropriate, which may lead to a review by Quora's moderation team. Thus, while users are encouraged to ask a wide range of questions, not all questions may remain visible on the platform if they violate these guidelines.",
